cafes.name: Orlando Cat Caf√©
cafes.address: 532 Cagan Park Ave Suite 201-203, Clermont, FL 34714, USA

text.text: 1st cat cafe in all of Florida, and it is amazing. The most shocking part is that the coffee, tea, and pastries are surprisingly really good. It is a fully functioning and clean cafe with a separate cat room. The cats are beautiful, and their coats shine and are super soft. They keep them on a strict diet, and it shows in the cat's coats and attitudes. Kid friendly and all of the cats and kittens are super social. Bathrooms are clean and staff are friendly. All sales go back to support the cats and shelter. There are even an assortment of jewlery, apparel, and other trinkets to purchase. Highly recommend visiting for some R&R with the cats or for adoption. All cats are spayed & and neutered, and all shots are up to date. Highly recommend

We were so lucky to spot this cafe from the highway, as a cat person I make sure to visit any cat cat wherever I travel.
You can see that this cafe really cares about cats sincerely. It was nice that it limited the number of people who could enter at once.  The cats looked healthy and happy. üê±üêæü§çüê±üêæü§çüê±üêæü§ç
The coffee shop was great..the sitting area very cozy, the coffee and passteries very delicious üòã

Fun cat cafe with lots of cats. Good and drinks are reasonably priced and taste great. Separate admission for 1 hour is $12 which is also reasonably priced. Cats are different daily and are all adoptable. 15 cats came in the day we visited so check often to see who  they have available for adoption

cafes.name: Kitty Cat Lounge
cafes.address: 946 E Orange St, Lakeland, FL 33801, USA

text.text: Very nice, clean cafe. Such cute decor. Very eco friendly operation. Cat room is clean.  If you fall in love with a kitty, they are adoptable!

Super cute lounge with friendly kitties and even friendlier staff. They also have coffee and pastries. I recommend the chocolate croissant because it's absolutely delicious. I recommend it for sure! ‚ù§Ô∏è

At the time I visited, a lot of the older cats were overwhelmed and hiding from the children but I adored them all the same. There were still other rambunctious kittens with endless energy anyway. I also tried a drink there and it was really good (can't remember the name but i think it had sorrel or Irish moss)

cafes.name: Purrology Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 5343 Florida Ave S, Lakeland, FL 33813, USA

text.text: This is such a wonderful idea to help save cats!! The owner fosters the cats at this cafe where people may go visit them and bond with them for adoption, should there be a connection with a cat. She has snacks/treats for sale, and the cats absolutely love them. She also sells teas and other drinks. I truly enjoyed my time. Thank you.

Went to a couple cat cafes in this area and this was the best one. The cats were all adorable and affectionate. The place is cute!  The drink menu was interesting and good! We were the only ones there near closing but it was worth it. I hope to come back one day :)

I just had my 16th birthday here and I‚Äôve never been happier! We come in and the owner immediately greets us, giving us the rundown and rules. She then sets up an area solely for my cake and presents, helps my mom set up, and even opens up a brand new pack of table cloth for us.
The atmosphere is so relaxing and welcoming. Various Taylor Swift eras played throughout the hour we were there, which was so fun‚Äî and I‚Äôm not even a Swiftie! The cats were all so adorable and playful, and one even chased my mom around whenever she got up. The cats are so happy and clearly well taken care of. The owner even offered treats for us to give to the cats, which was obviously so adorable to see.
When our hour in the room was up, the owner calmly told us she needed to set up for the next group, and proceeded to see us out to the main area. She was so sweet and allowed us to do presents and cake in the cafe, and even started a tab for my mom to buy trinkets and drinks for my friends and me.
Overall, we had SO MUCH fun and I‚Äôm ready to go back. If you‚Äôd like to test before adoption, or even just hang out with some kitties like we did, this is the place to go!

Just visited for the first time, this place is adorable and so friendly! The environment is a 10/10 for both the cats and the visitors, they really make sure the cats are comfortable and happy during this time ‚ù§Ô∏è. I love what you guys do for these cats and the drinks + cookies were surprisingly top tier! I assumed the food would be mediocre since people come for the cats not the cafe part (for the most part) but I gotta say all of the drinks and cookies we tried were just as awesome as the experience!

‚ÄúCats & Caffeine is an amazing establishment that not only serves great coffee but also helps cats find loving homes! The atmosphere is cozy and inviting, and the staff are incredibly friendly and helpful. It‚Äôs a perfect spot for cat lovers and coffee enthusiasts alike. I had a wonderful time and will definitely be back!‚Äù

Love the concept of cats & caffeine! We came on New Year‚Äôs Day and there was lots of kitties to love on, the space was clean and the employee, Lexie, was really nice and welcoming. We came in with no intention of adopting, and after spending an hour there.. we fell in love with kitty and now, a few days later, we are at home snuggling with her. It was a pleasant experience all around. The communication was prompt and we could really tell they care about the cats. I‚Äôd recommend going for a visit and loving on the kitties but would also strongly encourage you to adopt one (or two!) and support this small business. Pictures included of our little girl we adopted and some others we loved on while we visited.

cafes.name: Cattyshack Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 9902 Gulf Coast Main St D-140, Fort Myers, FL 33913, USA

text.text: Absolutely love this place!! I was taken away by the organization, cleanliness, and creativity put into the decorations and climbs. The cats ALL seem so relaxed and well-adjusted. Having ‚Äúhouse rules‚Äù is so appreciated and shows just how well these cats are cared for. Wonderful environment and cats all around. Shoutout to RACHEL for introducing us to the kitties and sharing lovely information and conversation! We will definitely be returning :)

Had an excellent time here. Cafe is great, everything is very tasty. The entire facility is super clean, they clean after each session in the playroom which is amazing. Cats look like they are very well taken care of, I highly recommend this place to anyone who wants a good snack or drink or just to play with some kitties/ adopt one if you fall in love!

My kids and I absolutely loved our first cat caf√© experience here! It was well worth the nearly two-hour drive.

We reserved a spot for a Sunday afternoon, and from the moment we arrived, the friendly staff made us feel welcome. The cat room was truly incredible‚Äîfar beyond what I expected. The setup is thoughtfully designed, with so many unique touches, like palm trees the cats can climb and lounge in and an adorable mini golf cart for them to explore. The interaction with the cats was fantastic, making the experience both fun and heartwarming.

The caf√© side of things did not disappoint either! My mocha frappe was excellent, my son loved his brownie, and my daughter enjoyed her frappe too. We also ordered food, which was just as delightful. The merchandise selection is a great bonus, with plenty of cute items to remember the visit.

Beyond the great atmosphere, food, and fun, I truly appreciate that this caf√© supports a wonderful cause. It‚Äôs clear they care deeply about the well-being of the cats and creating a positive experience for visitors.

I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for a unique and heartwarming outing.

It's all about the cats. Their beautiful babies are the sweetest. If one is too fiesta or simply does not want to be bothered, the staff are very attentive and careful to have them stay in their cage during your visit. Very clean and does not smell of litter boxes. New selection of cats all the time and they are adoptable. They have a range of ages from 6 months to 6+ years. There is a cutie pie to fit your personality and energy level. Lots of room to visit and play with the cats as well as an assortment of toys. You can order a coffee and sweet treat or just go and chill with the üò∫. Be sure to leave a donation as these sweet babies are not cheap to care for. Or better yet adopt one when you leave. Either way support this wonderful cat rescue!

Orlando, FL. Unlike other cat cafes I‚Äôve visited, the cats here are awake and contented. As the amiable owner explained, Bongo (the gray cat wearing a tie) watches out for all the cats. For example, a new shy kitty came out of her hiding place for the first time that day and Bongo came over to stand near, letting her know she was safe. The shop has a Bongo for President 2024 t-shirt for sale. He‚Äôs that magnificent. I‚Äôm disappointed he didn‚Äôt win the election. But you can join his grass roots campaign. Bongo for President 2028.

You don‚Äôt have to pay buku bucks to dine with the felines. If you want to study as you sip your amazing beverage (my friend loved her crafted lemonade) you can sit in the front room without the cat companions. The front room has a great atmosphere, too.

The room in the back with the kitties is priced very reasonably, though. I paid more for an hour at a cat cafe in Tampa. And this cafe has way more food and drink options.

There was a poodle lounging on the sofa in the front room when my friend and I arrived. As we stood watching the kitties in the back room the poodle ambled over to greet us. It was calm and friendly.

I got a chocolate chip cookie and chocolate chip muffin to go. My friend got her fruited lemonade. Everything we got was fresh, delicious, and not overpriced.

Most of the patrons were quiet individuals in high school or college.

They had cute merchandise. I loved their cat collars without bells.

Highly recommend!

Amazing place!!! Half kitty rescue, half kitty adoption, and half a delicious cafe!!  There are currently 21 cats waiting for homes (we may have taken care of one!), but they have placed over 800 already done 2019!!  The avocado toast is fantastic, as are their coffees!!  If you are anywhere near The Kitty Beautiful, you need to stop in and have a bite, see the cats, and maybe take one home!!

cafes.name: Sassy Cat Club Cafe
cafes.address: 735 W Lumsden Rd, Brandon, FL 33511, USA

text.text: Very cute spot where you can unwind with adoptable kitties that are rescued.  All the kitties are well taken care of and everything is very clean. The owner is extremely friendly and really has a mission of saving cats!

If you love cats, this is the place to visit!! What a great experience The joy of a cats love is out of this world. If you need some cat love ‚ù§Ô∏è make sure to check this place. We will be returning soon.

Loved watching all the cats everywhere. It was really cool to see that some were up for adoption too. The host/owner was really nice as well! She had plenty of toys and activities for the cats, and clever food/water/litterbox stations. Definitely took some notes for home. Highly recommend making a reservation!

cafes.name: PURe JOY CAT CAFE
cafes.address: 1120 Beville Rd Suite C, Daytona Beach, FL 32114, USA

text.text:
This cat cafe is clean, very well maintained, and always a pleasure to visit! By far the best cat cafe we have been to. You can tell that everyone here loves what they do and truly cares for all of the cats/kittens. I also love that they work with other local rescues that would otherwise not receive the same exposure!

We adopted our sweet Mouse from here -in conjunction with Paws & Tails rescue- about 8 months ago and she has fit right in with our resident cat. We told Frank we were looking to adopt and he pointed us right to cats that fit exactly what we were looking for. She has proven to be just that and more! She is so social, playful, and loving.

Even if you are not looking to adopt, this is a great place to visit and enjoy some kitty company. They also have a gift shop in the front entrance that is full of cat related gifts.

Thank you Frank, Isaac, and team for running this cafe for a great cause. I am so glad we could support you and will continue to do so for the foreseeable future!

I can‚Äôt own a cat currently and this was a great way to get a little dose of cat. My only wish is that it was a little more spacious. The spaces are fairly small and a little stuffy. You get a cookie and a drink which are pretty basic but you‚Äôre really there for the cats anyway. üòÅ All of the cats seem healthy and there are plenty of places for them to go and get out of reach or isolate if they‚Äôre not feeling up to socializing. I loved the little board with all the cats‚Äô details and especially how several of them had clearly been chewed on. üòÇ the owner and some other customers were both very friendly. All in all, a very nice time.

Absolutely wonderful cat cafe ran by the most caring staff and owner. You can book your session online but they do accept walk-ins.

We came in on a Saturday to play with the cats. We fell in love with Felix and Mr. Jigsaw after meeting them once and they were home with us only a few days later. They are becoming the best of friends and love being at their forever home.

If you‚Äôre looking to adopt or just hang out with the most adorable cats, stop by and visit Frank and Isaac and PURe Joy.

cafes.name: Feeline Good Cat Caf√©
cafes.address: 201 SE 2nd Pl Suite 113, Gainesville, FL 32601, USA

text.text: I had to write this review because I got my beloved cat here. Her name is gum drop, a 10 month old white kitten. I got her in 2023 December 28th. I love her and am so happy I got her only hours after she arrived at the Cafe. Thank you to this cafe and organization that gave me my little girl cat
Great place to study, the cats are amazing!! The staff are really nice and kind, too.

It‚Äôs absolutely the cutest little coffee shop ! The ladies behind the counter were so sweet and welcoming, we had our toddler with us and ordered him a hot chocolate and she made sure to make it not too hot and they even drew little cats on the cups witch is adorable! Definitely would recommend to anyone who loves cats or coffee , will absolutely be back !!

cafes.name: DeLand Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 844 E New York Ave Unit B, DeLand, FL 32724, USA

text.text: We came from Pittsburg Kansas to go to Disney, and also to visit the DeLand Cat Cafe! The owner was super helpful, resourceful, and also gave us a few other places to visit in the area during our trip! I have been looking forward to going to this cafe/adoption center for a few weeks now, and it did NOT disappoint! I grabbed a few pictures while I was there, and all of these cats are adoptable!! They were all super friendly and loving, and even the ‚Äúbad kitty‚Äù was friendly and allowed pets (although not for longü§≠) But, it was a super cute place, and I would 100% go again when I‚Äôm in the area!! The owner also saves mostly euthanasia risk kitties and gives them a second chance! Awesome place to spend an hour or two, with low rates!!

We started our visit with lunch at the cafe, enjoying their delicious pancakes and avocado toast‚Äîboth were fantastic, and the staff was incredibly friendly. After our meal, we headed over to the cat area. The space is cozy, with plenty of seating and tables to set your coffee down if you brought one along from the cafe side.

The highlight, of course, was the cats! There were kitties everywhere, each with their own unique personality. For just 25 cents, you can even buy treats to give them, which was a fun way to interact. We also visited the kitten room‚Äîa separate section in the same building‚Äîwhere you can meet the little ones.

The atmosphere was relaxed and inviting, making it a perfect spot for kids (who know how to handle cats gently), a day date, or anyone who loves spending time with felines. Highly recommend visiting.

We had a wonderful experience at the DeLand Cat Caf√©! This place is a gem for cat lovers and an amazing addition to the community. The caf√© is filled with adorable, friendly cats, all looking for their forever homes. The staff is incredibly knowledgeable and passionate about helping these cats find the perfect match.

We were lucky enough to meet and adopt the sweetest girl, and we couldn‚Äôt be happier with our new furry family member! The adoption process was smooth, and it was clear that the caf√© puts the cats‚Äô well-being first.

Whether you're looking to adopt or just spend some time cuddling with cats in a relaxing environment, the DeLand Cat Caf√© is a must-visit. It's a heartwarming place that‚Äôs doing fantastic work for rescue cats. Highly recommend! üêæüíï

cafes.name: The Witty Whisker Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 112 N Ponce De Leon Blvd Unit A, St. Augustine, FL 32084, USA

text.text:
We absolutely loved this place!! Not only were there so many amazing cats to hang out with, but the food and drinks were also really good. I feel like a lot of cafes like this offer free Keurig coffee or something, but their menu offered really delicious coffee drinks and food. It was Valentine‚Äôs Day when we went and they had a special menu: the Chocolate Covered Strawberry Latte was so good!

My daughter is 16 months and had a blast. All of the cats were super friendly and the staff and other visitors were very kind to her, which is always a plus. The place itself was also very cute, with lots of cat-related art and other items for purchase. Definitely recommend checking this place out!

My friends and I attended a meowditaion yoga class and it was so much fun. The cats are too cute, the owner provided a great meditation and yin yoga session, then we grabbed some coffee! We‚Äôll definitely be back for painting with cats and their cat sound bath!

This place is very fun! The cats are friendly and sociable and it isn't overly expensive. The food and drinks were also good, and the little knick knacks you can buy in the front are very cute! The coffee was also very good. The only thing was that I ordered a "fresh" biscuit which was kind of expensive for being just a cold, definitely pre-frozen biscuit. However, I appreciate that all the cats are rescues and are up for adoption !

cafes.name: Frisky Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 1092 S Ponce De Leon Blvd, St. Augustine, FL 32084, USA

text.text: Our attendant, first of all, was AMAZING! The food was DELICIOUS! Highly recommend the macaroons! The coffee was 5 stars! If you see any reviews about it not being ‚Äúkid friendly‚Äù, it‚Äôs not true. You just have to watch your kids to make sure they‚Äôre following the rules of the cat room- like any other cat cafe, Otherwise they will be told to follow the rules, again like any other public place!

I went here with my friends and absolutely LOVED it!! The people here are SO kind and helpful, and the cats are SO sweet. The food and drinks were amazing, and there was such a wide variety to choose from! Overall a 10/10 experience, and I can't wait to go back!

Cats were adorable. They have a huge room with lots of cats to interact with, which was really nice. I will say, it smelled really bad inside, both in the cafe and in the cat room; we eventually got used to it, but wanted to warn people who are sensitive to cat smells. That was our main complaint. Other than that, we had a great time with the kitties.

cafes.name: The Kitty Cup
cafes.address: 1461 SW Gatlin Blvd, Port St. Lucie, FL 34953, USA

text.text: Very small quaint cafe with a large window to the Kitty room . Kitty room is much bigger, which is the main focus! To mingle with the cats and hopefully find their forever homes! I came to check out the place not, quite readyto adopt,  since I'm still getting over the loss of my last fur baby. Volunteers were very friendly and I got a kitty fix! It's wonderful that they work with The Humane Society of the Treasure Coast. I ended up purchasing a necklace for a gift for a Friend for an upcoming birthday. Highly recommend a visit, even if you're not adopting (but that would be great-they just got their 300 cat adopted while I was there), every purchase, and every visit helps keep the cats fed and safe until they find their forever homes.

We were visiting the Kitty Cup as a one year memorial to my mother who passed away September of 2023. She adored cats and loved her tea. Perfect family get-together, and one of my siblings adopted one of the snugly kitties. Very nice family experience. We have some out of town guests in November and we'll come back! The staff is friendly and informative. The facility is clean and set up nicely.

I went to the kitty cup for the first time for yoga night, and what an amazing experience!!! Walking in I was greeted by the cutest coffeeshop, the decor is beautiful, trendy, and comforting, and it smells great.

I was shocked by how clean and good the whole place smelled. I was surrounded by cats and it felt cleaner than my own home.

The yoga itself was so fun, playful and relaxing that I can't wait to make another reservation.

Thank you for bringing the kitty cup into our community!

cafes.name: Catnip Caf√© and Lounge
cafes.address: 202 S Collins St, Plant City, FL 33563, USA

text.text:
Such a seriously cute place!! Unfortunately we didn't come prepared for the cost to hangout in the adoption center so I wanted to share the details we got today to keep anyone else from being ill-prepared for kitty snuggles. There is a cost for the cuddle time, it is $10 per 30 minutes or $15 for a full hour of feline fun! The cost is to help care for the kitties and is SO worth it!

We will be going back very soon to play.

However, the coffee bar and pastries looked amazing all on their own! Prices were great and the service was even better!

The ladies at this place were beyond welcoming and ever so kind. Can't wait to go visit them again soon!

Not just for kids you guys feel amazing with decent cats üêà well maintained and trained by family owners. Most hot spot to visit in plant city downtown.
I love this French coffee ‚òïÔ∏è
You‚Äôll find cozy indoor plants.

Beautiful and welcoming decor. Friendly staff that make it feel inviting to just sit down and spend time with others. There are plenty of cats you can spend time with for a small donation. They are super friendly, and if I could I would have taken one of them with me. I'm not sure what there adoption process looks like, but I know that you can adopt these beautiful babies from them. Oh! And crystals! That was a fun little surprise I wasn't expecting. I will probably come visit again some time soon.

cafes.name: Good Luck Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 901 Progresso Dr #202, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

text.text:
I had a wonderful time at Good Luck Cat Cafe! The entrance is free, and the space is so cozy and welcoming. The ladies who take care of the cats are incredibly kind and clearly love what they do. I had the chance to chat with Ginette (I hope I spelled that right!), and she was such a lovely person ü•∞

The cats are adorable and well cared for, making the experience even more special. I highly recommend this place to any cat lover! I can‚Äôt wait to visit again soon

Had a lovely 30 minutes playing with some beautiful cats üòä whilst not a cafe per se, the experience was really nice. Everyone there is so passionate and the cats look so, so healthy and looked after. If only I could have snuck a couple on the plane ü§î thank you üíö

Such a wonderful place! Enter is free, the cats are not in cages here, they run freely. The volunteers are very nice, all donations and money go to their cats (also you can adopt a cat) It's very cute, calming and of course you can play with them.

cafes.name: Tally Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 2218 N Monroe St, Tallahassee, FL 32303, USA

text.text: all of the staff is so kind and the kitties are adorable!! the drinks they serve are delicious and are made with lots of love.

I've been coming here regularly for a while now. It's a really wonderful cat cafe that I would encourage anyone to check out!

All of the kitties are adoptable. Some have been there a while, and it's fun to see familiar faces, but it's even better to see that a favorite kitty is gone because that means they've found their family. They're always bringing in new kitties, so each visit is special and unique.

While there's a $10 entrance fee for the cat room, you can also just order a coffee and hang out in the cafe section. You will still see plenty of cats.

The coffee and teas are great, and I have never gotten bad service here. Everyone is very friendly.

Such a wonderful cafe. The employees were so friendly from the moment we walked in. The boba teas were so yummy and of course the cats were so sweet. You can tell they truly care about the animals and give them a great life. Can‚Äôt wait to visit again.

cafes.name: Fat Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 2901 E Park Ave, Tallahassee, FL 32301, USA

text.text:
It's a cat cafe. It's an instant cure for depression. Every kitten is absolutely adorable. And they all have the sweetest personalities.

The cafe gives a variety of toys for the customers to interact with the cats, but the best part is when they get in your lap and cuddle you.

I will be visiting this place often. Love it so much.

I booked the cafe for two hours with a friend and we both loved it. We went during less busy hours so we had the room to ourselves which was much nicer than having other people with us.

Most of the cats are friendly and want to be petted while some are more shy. There are many toys on a counter to play with them but they provide endless entertainment just being themselves. Along with the cats, the jazz music helps create a super relaxing atmosphere. Fair price for the amount of stress relieving this place does for you!!

Great place to see and interact with some kitties.  The cafe part needs a little work as its Keurig and some bottled sodas in a messy fridge.  Hope they can get some good coffee in there one day.  Nevertheless a very cool place to visit.  Had a lot of fun.

cafes.name: Caffeinated Cat
cafes.address: 331 1st Ave N, Jacksonville Beach, FL 32250, USA

text.text: This is a wonderful place.  Could there be a better combo?   Cats and coffeeüêà‚Äç‚¨õ‚òïÔ∏è. I don‚Äôt think so.  They have cat named seasonal coffee drinks that were just plain delicious and you can sip your coffee while hanging out with the kittiesüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª.   Definitely recommend. You will feel so good supporting such a fantastic cause when you grab your daily cup of Joe and you may just find your new furry companion üôåüèªüôåüèªüêà‚Äç‚¨õ

Caffeinated Cat is primarily a rescue center for cats with medical issues.  We really enjoyed interacting with the kitties that weren't shy that day and hopefully making their day a bit brighter with funds from our presence, drink purchases, and swag purchases.  If coming with children, just be aware of the time limitations and state of the cats.

The cat room is really cute with lots of cat themed kitty condos and places to sit, relax, jump, and hide.

I was hoping for some more food options and more places to sit and enjoy a drink and food. The cats were kind of peopled out by the time we got there, so I recommend going earlier in the day.

That being said, it's a quaint place with a really cool cat room. There's lots of places to sit in the cat room, and the setup for the cats is really cool. The drinks were really good and staff is so sweet and helpful.
